title: Chinese Consulate General in Kuching donates 2,000 masks and 500 protective suits to Sarawak General Hospital in April 2020 (Linked to Project ID#90408)
description: On April 24, 2020, the Chinese Consulate General in Kuching provided a donation of 2,000 medical masks and 500 protective suits to the Sarawak General Hospital in Malaysia. This donation is intended to aid the hospital in combatting COVID-19. The monetary value of the donation is unknown.  This is the first of two batches of medical supplies provided by the Chinese Consulate General to Sarawak General Hospital. The details of the second batch are captured in Project ID #90408.
staff_comments: AidData has estimated the transaction amount for this donation based on price catalogues from the World Health Organization (WHO). Please see the TUFF Methodology for additional details.

title: Changsha High Tech Industrial Development Zone donates 10,300 masks to Malaysia-China Friendship Association
description: On March 26, 2020, the Malaysia-China Friendship Association announced that 10,000 masks and 3,000 N95 masks were being donated by Changsha High Tech Industrial Development Zone to the association. On March 31, the supply arrived in Malaysia. The donation will go toward the frontline in the fight against COVID-19 in Malaysia.

title: Chinese Embassy in Malaysia donates RM 200,000 to Malaysia-China Friendship Association for Youth Exchange Fund (Linked to Project ID#66241, #86967)
description: On September 24, 2020, the Chinese Embassy in Malaysia donated RM 200,000 to Malaysia-China Friendship Association. The donation goes to the Youth Exchange Fund where Malaysian youth go to China to learn about culture, education, business, and lifestyle through Chinese Universities.  This is part of a larger set of donations from the embassy to the Youth Exchange Fund (see #86967, #66241).

title: Chinese Consulate General in Penang donates 15,000 masks to Penang State Government

This donation is intended to aid Penang against Covid-19. After the donation ceremony, the Penang State Government transferred the masks to the Penang General Hospital where patients of Covid-19 are treated.

title: Malaysia-China Kuantan Industrial Park and other Chinese companies donate 20,000 masks to Peneng General Hospital (Linked to Project ID#93993, 93994)
description: On April 9, 2020, Chinese companies Beibu Gulf Holdings (Malaysia) (Project ID#93993), Zhongxin Resource Regeneration Technology Malaysia Sdn Bhd (Project ID#93994), and Malaysia-China Kuantan Industrial Park (Project ID#90423) donated 10,000 N95 masks and 10,000 medical face masks to the Penang General Hospital to support Malaysia during the COVID-19 pandemic. The monetary value of the donation is unknown.
staff_comments: 1. Because Beibu Golf Holding, Zhongxin Resource Regeneration Technology Malaysia Sdn Bhd, and Malaysia-China Kuantan Industrial Park all contributed an unknown number of supplies to this donation, AidData assumes each donor made an equal contribution. The total value of the donation is estimated to be $14,000, with each donor contributing USD 4,666.66 (USD 14,000 / 3 known contributors = USD 4,666.66).
